conditioning drills 
you watch them to make sure theyre sweating said davenport 
north coach cy robinson who said his twohour afternoon practices 
would be cut back 30 minutes 
grain and soybean futures posted their strongest gains in a week 
monday in response to predictions that crops in the droughtweary 
corn belt would bake for most of this week 
mondays midday weather forecasts coming on the heels of a hot 
mostly dry weekend in the midwest stoked fears of further damage 
to the crops and helped push most corn oat and soybean contracts 
up their permitted daily limits on the chicago board of trade 
seven weekend heatrelated deaths in chicago have brought the 
cook county total to 28 since the recordbreaking heat wave began 
county officials said 
