<TEXT>
the us trade deficit suffered a major 
setback in june swelling to 125 billion the government said 
today in a report that sent the dollar down sharply although 
briefly on foreign currency markets 
the surge in the trade deficit a sharp 285 percent worse than 
the revised may imbalance of 98 billion came after three 
consecutive months of improving trade figures the commerce 
department reported 
junes trading shortfall was the worst since februarys 144 
billion deficit which triggered a 100point plunge in the dow 
